{"word":"κηδεμών","slug":"κηδεμών","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κηδεμών</b></el> <el>(κηδεμών, όνος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>κηδέω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>one who is in charge</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> for burial, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>a protector, guardian</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—also of a female, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:κηδεστής'><el>κηδεστής</el></a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}